description:
Witnessing to others is already difficult. Witnessing to doubting atheists can seem almost impossible. Oftentimes, unbelievers have aggressive and pressing questions, and these questions can be extremely challenging to answer if you are not prepared. How can we do God justice and give intelligent answers? Are there definite true answers, or, is truth relative? Wes Peppers goes through some popular arguments and gives some insight on how to witness to an atheist who believes some of these popular arguments against the existence of God.

For more, please visit:
https://amazingdiscoveries.org
https://amazingdiscoveries.tv
